A '''food-feed system''' is an integrated [[livestock]]-crop production system where crops grown on farms are harvested for human consumption and the crop-residues or by-products are used as feed for livestock.  For example,  intercropping of [[cowpea]]s between rows of [[cassava]]. The [[legume]]s can enrich soil fertility and enhance the crop productivity. Further the [[cassava hay]] can be used as dairy feed.

